    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just about the money or the debt. it's the fact that i ruined the life they thought we had. they look at me and see the man who was supposed to build something, and now they just see a failure. i feel like if i'm not the provider, i'm nothing. staying here and watching them suffer through the fallout of my mistakes feels more cruel than just... not being a burden anymore. it feels like the only way to actually protect them from the wreckage is to just stop being part of it.",
